36:23.920 --> 36:26.520
Housemaid wanted.

36:26.600 --> 36:28.600
State councillor Benda.

36:36.280 --> 36:38.760
-Is this the exact wording?
-Yes.

36:39.080 --> 36:40.080
Very good.

36:41.920 --> 36:44.120
Any other new findings?

36:46.000 --> 36:47.480
Unforeseen risks?

36:49.080 --> 36:51.880
I'm invisible. I'm sure of it.

36:53.320 --> 36:55.600
You must never be sure of anything.

36:58.280 --> 36:59.440
Of course.

37:00.720 --> 37:02.840
You know how sensitive this affair is.

37:04.160 --> 37:06.920
At some point the decisive clue
will present itself.

37:07.880 --> 37:10.280
We must not miss this moment.

37:10.840 --> 37:12.680
I know, Mr. Councillor.

37:16.120 --> 37:19.640
-You're doing a good job, Stefan.
-Thank you.

37:21.320 --> 37:24.080
But strike the word "security"
from your vocabulary.

37:24.160 --> 37:25.240
Yes, sir.

37:49.040 --> 37:52.360
-Excuse me.
-Wow! You look good.

37:53.920 --> 37:55.920
How charming! Come.

38:16.040 --> 38:17.560
-Evening.
-Evening.

38:22.600 --> 38:25.120
<i>Bellissima! </i>How you light up our house.

38:26.600 --> 38:28.640
Shall we go powder our nose?

38:29.600 --> 38:30.760
I'll be right back.

38:39.440 --> 38:42.960
<i>Then I always only think of you</i>

38:45.880 --> 38:49.320
<i>Then I always think of you</i>

38:52.520 --> 38:54.240
<i>And I tell myself</i>

38:55.200 --> 38:59.640
<i>My rose, stay and never forget me</i>

39:13.560 --> 39:14.640
Inspector?

39:19.480 --> 39:20.480
Mr. GrÃ¤f!

39:21.400 --> 39:24.520
-I didn't expect you here.
-I didn't expect you, either.

39:27.080 --> 39:28.480
Excuse me.

39:29.480 --> 39:30.400
And good evening.

39:31.320 --> 39:33.800
-Amazing as always.
-Same goes for you.

39:34.160 --> 39:35.640
Hello, darling.

39:35.720 --> 39:37.760
Long time no see. Everything fine?

39:37.840 --> 39:40.240
-Yes. And yourself?
-Good.

39:40.320 --> 39:42.120
I'll have what he's having.

39:43.000 --> 39:44.840
Lemonade for the lady.

39:45.640 --> 39:48.160
What? With a shot, please.

39:48.240 --> 39:49.400
And you?
Thanks.

39:49.480 --> 39:51.280
I have to go back to my family.

39:51.360 --> 39:52.640
Inspector.

40:05.120 --> 40:07.640
Is that Trechkov? On stage?

40:09.720 --> 40:11.880
Yes, that's him.
We'll meet him in the break.

40:18.440 --> 40:19.640
Shall we?

40:24.840 --> 40:26.600
Oh, Kardakov.

40:27.880 --> 40:30.400
He's wasting his talent, the moron.

40:30.720 --> 40:34.160
I hate him.
He's so gifted you have to hate him.

40:35.120 --> 40:37.840
I told him, you are our real star.

40:38.160 --> 40:40.800
Your crazy violin is of the devil.

40:40.880 --> 40:43.360
And he goes off to play revolution.

40:43.440 --> 40:46.240
I hate him. I hate that fortress.

40:46.680 --> 40:49.320
-The Red Fortress, right?
-The whole bunch is crazy.

40:49.400 --> 40:51.720
They actually think
they could topple Stalin.

40:52.200 --> 40:54.680
The whole thing is a ghastly idiocy.

40:54.800 --> 41:00.080
The leader, Trotsky, is down in Turkey,
wasting the lives of other people.

41:00.160 --> 41:02.320
-I hate him.
-What about the countess,

41:02.400 --> 41:04.440
-Ms. Sorokina?
-Oh, her.

41:05.680 --> 41:07.360
She's made it all worse.

41:08.720 --> 41:10.160
She's turned his head.

41:11.200 --> 41:13.000
Then she ran off with him.

41:14.200 --> 41:15.480
I hate her.

41:16.160 --> 41:17.800
Where could this Kardakov be?

41:18.840 --> 41:21.680
I swore I would keep it to myself, but...

41:23.400 --> 41:25.560
discretion is not my passion.

41:28.840 --> 41:30.360
In KÃ¶penick.

41:33.000 --> 41:34.600
At Wormsstrasse.

41:35.320 --> 41:37.000
There's some kind of basement.

41:37.760 --> 41:39.520
In there is a printer's.

41:41.080 --> 41:41.960
And?

41:43.080 --> 41:45.480
It's the headquarter of the Red Fortress. -I love that piece.
-So do I.

42:00.880 --> 42:03.600
-What?
-Want to dance?

42:03.680 --> 42:04.640
Are you serious? Are you married, by the way?

42:25.120 --> 42:25.960
No.

42:26.240 --> 42:27.600
But going steady?

42:27.840 --> 42:28.800
It's not that simple.

42:30.200 --> 42:32.280
"Love is not simple.
It's very complicated.

